# Cursor rules language (Golden English)

## Requirement

Every file under **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** in this repository **must** be authored in **English (en-US)**. That includes narrative text, headings, checklist items, tables, examples, and the **`description` field** in YAML frontmatter.

Exception: **identifiers** unchanged by language (routes, filenames, CLI flags, table names in SQL, quoted code, etc.) stay as-is when they mirror the codebase.

## User-facing copy vs Cursor rules

**Do not** use `.cursor/rules` as storage for strings shown to learners, parents, or staff on the live site.

User-visible wording belongs in **`src/dictionaries/`** and follows **`.cursor/rules/09-i18n-copy.mdc`**.

## Semantics when editing rules

Translating or editing a rule **must not change its intent**. Preserve cross-references to other rules (**`03-architecture.mdc`**, **`12-supabase-app-boundaries.mdc`**, etc.), repository paths in backticks, and technical contracts described in sibling files.
